{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As the Joint Management Body (JMB) tasked with maintaining the PPR Kota Damansara blocks; PHSSB can leverage on the Aduanku platform for monitoring and keeping the residents updated about the issues reported by them.\line All we need is the email of the PHSSB staff assigned to monitor Aduanku and they can be added in by Sinar Project.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 The Dashboard is available to the Public Body to have an overview of the issues and what needs to be given priority to be addressed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/leowmjw/my-articles/master/SINARPROJECT/OPENSPENDING/ADUANKU/assets/Aduanku_Dashboard_View_PublicBody.png]\cf0}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 They can easily update the status as work goes in progress and actions are taken. In the screeshots below, the PHSSB staff assigned just updates the state of each issue:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/leowmjw/my-articles/master/SINARPROJECT/OPENSPENDING/ADUANKU/assets/Dashboard_Status_View_For_PublicBody.png]\cf0}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To highlight some of the status and how it is best used:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 - Investigating: Do add any other pertinent findings in the update\line
- Action Scheduled: Do update when a fix is scheduled so the resident knows \line
- In Progress: Inform the resident that a fix is ongoing so thy are aware\line
- Unable to fix: Please detail why this cannot be done\line
- Not Responsible: If falls under MBPJ; please help file on behalf of the \line
resident\line
- Fixed: Attach picture to show the problem has been fixed  \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This ends the quick review over the possible scenarios; if there are anything not covered, contact us at Sinar Project for assistant to get it resolved.\par}
